SIMPLE: malt
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Malt
<hw>Malt</hw> <pr>(m⟦add⟧lt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>mealt</ets>; akin to D. <ets>mout</ets>, G. <ets>malz</ets>, Icel.,
Sw., & Dan. <ets>malt</ets>, and E. <ets>melt</ets>. ⟦root⟧108. See
<er>Melt</er>.]</ety> <def>Barley or other grain, steeped in water and
dried in a kiln, thus forcing germination until the saccharine principle
has been evolved. It is used in brewing and in the distillation of
whisky.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Malt</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Malt
<hw>Malt</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Relating to, containing, or made with,
malt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Malt liquor</b></col>, <cd>an alcoholic liquor, as beer,
ale, porter, etc., prepared by fermenting an infusion of malt.</cd> --
<col><b>Malt dust</b></col>, <cd>fine particles of malt, or of the grain
used in making malt; -- used as a fertilizer.</cd> ⟦ldquo⟧ <xex>Malt
dust</xex> consists chiefly of the infant radicle separated from the
grain.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Sir H. Davy.</au> -- <col><b>Malt floor</b></col>,
<cd>a floor for drying malt.</cd> -- <mcol><col><b>Malt house</b></col>,
<it>or</it> <col><b>Malthouse</b></col></mcol>, <cd>a house in which
malt is made.</cd> -- <col><b>Malt kiln</b></col>, <cd>a heated chamber
for drying malt.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Malt</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Malt
<hw>Malt</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Malted</conjf>: <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Malting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To make into malt; <as>as, to
<ex>malt</ex> barley</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Malt</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Malt
<hw>Malt</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To become malt; also, to make grain
into malt.</def> <rj><au>Mortimer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

